WEBVTT

1
00:00:05.100 --> 00:00:07.383
We claim attacks on these foreign ships.

2
00:00:09.191 --> 00:00:10.995
There will be no sleep tonight

3
00:00:11.019 --> 00:00:14.520
until the West and their
occupation is driven from our land.

4
00:00:14.544 --> 00:00:17.084
Leave my country!

5
00:00:17.765 --> 00:00:19.264
We will find you.

6
00:00:19.288 --> 00:00:21.755
We will attack you wherever you are.

7
00:00:24.816 --> 00:00:29.763
Remember. this attack was not the end.

8
00:00:30.212 --> 00:00:32.434
This is only the beginning.

9
00:00:49.666 --> 00:00:51.660
How's the coffee here?

10
00:00:52.408 --> 00:00:53.845
I've had better.

11
00:01:00.677 --> 00:01:02.655
Not what you expected. huh?

12
00:01:02.679 --> 00:01:04.874
Well. to be honest.
when the embassy said

13
00:01:04.898 --> 00:01:07.225
a woman came in hoping to trade
secrets on the drone attack.

14
00:01:07.249 --> 00:01:09.662
I was expecting a little more. um...

15
00:01:09.686 --> 00:01:11.614
Desperate and disheveled victim?

16
00:01:11.638 --> 00:01:13.300
Yeah.

17
00:01:13.324 --> 00:01:15.756
I mean. a Chanel blazer
doesn't exactly scream help me.

18
00:01:15.780 --> 00:01:17.644
I don't need your pity.

19
00:01:18.434 --> 00:01:22.501
I need a deal. and I want asylum.

20
00:01:22.525 --> 00:01:25.504
A businesswoman. OK.

21
00:01:25.528 --> 00:01:27.113
What are you offering?

22
00:01:27.137 --> 00:01:30.576
The man responsible for the
attack on one of your ships.

23
00:01:30.925 --> 00:01:32.826
Abdul Akkad.

24
00:01:34.102 --> 00:01:36.663
Abdul Akkad.
the Syrian terrorist leader.

25
00:01:39.325 --> 00:01:42.433
Well. if you can give us Akkad's
location. we'll give you asylum.

26
00:01:42.457 --> 00:01:44.567
I don't have that.

27
00:01:45.993 --> 00:01:47.439
So what do you have?

28
00:01:47.463 --> 00:01:49.384
A way in.

29
00:01:49.770 --> 00:01:52.531
I'm a wealth manager based in Istanbul.

30
00:01:52.555 --> 00:01:54.490
Work for the Levni Company.

31
00:01:54.514 --> 00:01:57.754
a family run oil refinery
on the Turkish border.

32
00:01:57.778 --> 00:02:02.237
Their money. it was green
for a good long while.

33
00:02:02.261 --> 00:02:03.847
but now it's stained with blood.

34
00:02:03.871 --> 00:02:06.328
They're in business with Abdul Akkad.

35
00:02:06.352 --> 00:02:07.895
OK.

36
00:02:07.919 --> 00:02:09.486
How do you know they're in business?

37
00:02:09.510 --> 00:02:11.289
I saw a suspicious transfer.

38
00:02:11.313 --> 00:02:15.554
a multi-million dollar
transaction to a Shell company.

39
00:02:15.578 --> 00:02:17.992
I dug in. linked it to Akkad.

40
00:02:18.016 --> 00:02:19.907
The Levnis are funding his attacks.

41
00:02:19.931 --> 00:02:23.562
And how exactly are we
supposed to get the Levnis to talk?

42
00:02:23.586 --> 00:02:26.652
Selma Levni lives in New York.

43
00:02:26.676 --> 00:02:29.177
She is getting married
here this weekend.

44
00:02:29.201 --> 00:02:32.702
I could get you in there as my plus one.

45
00:02:32.726 --> 00:02:35.270
The rest is up to you.

46
00:02:37.432 --> 00:02:45.432
Synced & corrected by -robtor-
www.addic7ed.com

47
00:02:53.965 --> 00:02:55.507
Kimberly Graham.

48
00:02:55.531 --> 00:02:57.359
Oh. we can remove those cuffs. can't we?

49
00:03:01.251 --> 00:03:02.253
How are you?

50
00:03:02.277 --> 00:03:04.516
Patrick is back from London.

51
00:03:04.540 --> 00:03:06.779
De-radicalization camp.

52
00:03:06.803 --> 00:03:09.347
- Anthony filed for divorce.
- Thank you.

53
00:03:09.371 --> 00:03:12.307
And you cannot get
a decent manicure in here.

54
00:03:12.331 --> 00:03:14.613
So they lied on the website. huh?

55
00:03:14.637 --> 00:03:16.658
I'm guessing this
isn't a wellness visit.

56
00:03:16.682 --> 00:03:18.356
How perceptive.

57
00:03:18.380 --> 00:03:21.011
I can't stop thinking about
how those Keown mercenaries

58
00:03:21.035 --> 00:03:22.795
knew Colin and me were at the lake house

59
00:03:22.819 --> 00:03:24.623
with your husband and stepson.

60
00:03:24.647 --> 00:03:27.191
Yeah. strange.

61
00:03:27.215 --> 00:03:29.846
A remote location no one
should have known about.

62
00:03:29.870 --> 00:03:32.004
yet they knew exactly where we were.

63
00:03:32.028 --> 00:03:33.806
It was like they had inside information.

64
00:03:33.830 --> 00:03:37.409
Huh. It is kind of like that.

65
00:03:38.879 --> 00:03:42.928
- What do you want?
- Freedom.

66
00:03:42.952 --> 00:03:45.209
How about library work
instead of porter duty?

67
00:03:45.233 --> 00:03:47.255
I don't mind a little bleach.

68
00:03:47.279 --> 00:03:48.646
Well. I can always call
the U.S. attorney

69
00:03:48.670 --> 00:03:50.631
and have them move you to
a minimum-security facility.

70
00:03:50.655 --> 00:03:51.962
You can do better.

71
00:03:51.986 --> 00:03:54.051
Now you're just wasting my time.

72
00:03:55.026 --> 00:03:56.114
Wait.

73
00:03:58.638 --> 00:04:00.596
You have a deal.

74
00:04:03.817 --> 00:04:07.797
There's a company that gathers
information from spies.

75
00:04:07.821 --> 00:04:13.324
They have moles in MI6. FSB. the CIA.

76
00:04:13.348 --> 00:04:16.961
They told Keown your location that day.

77
00:04:17.366 --> 00:04:19.534
This company have a name?

78
00:04:20.660 --> 00:04:22.412
I don't have all day.

79
00:04:23.271 --> 00:04:25.206
Pyramid Security.

80
00:04:28.624 --> 00:04:30.428
Yeah. hold on.

81
00:04:30.452 --> 00:04:34.824
So you're telling me
that Colin is the mole?

82
00:04:34.848 --> 00:04:36.521
Well. someone in
the CIA is feeding intel

83
00:04:36.545 --> 00:04:38.175
to Pyramid Security.
and I'll remind you.

84
00:04:38.199 --> 00:04:40.873
that's where Colin's
girlfriend Sarah works.

85
00:04:40.897 --> 00:04:43.336
Right. But could it be a coincidence?

86
00:04:43.360 --> 00:04:45.052
Yeah. could be. but why
would he keep her a secret?

87
00:04:45.076 --> 00:04:47.145
I mean. you seem pretty sold on this.

88
00:04:47.169 --> 00:04:50.169
Look. I don't want to be. That's
just where the evidence is pointing.

89
00:04:50.193 --> 00:04:51.449
All right. well. you've got a theory.

90
00:04:51.473 --> 00:04:53.886
and now you have to make it a case.

91
00:04:53.910 --> 00:04:56.498
So follow the evidence.
see where it goes.

92
00:04:56.522 --> 00:04:58.891
Right. I'll be in touch.

93
00:04:58.915 --> 00:05:01.159
OK.

94
00:05:05.705 --> 00:05:07.900
Hey. What do you think of these?

95
00:05:07.924 --> 00:05:10.033
Wife got 'em for me.
Is it too much or...

96
00:05:10.057 --> 00:05:11.513
Hmm.

97
00:05:11.537 --> 00:05:13.080
Barking up the wrong tree there. Larry.

98
00:05:13.104 --> 00:05:15.355
Bill's idea of flashy is a blue shirt.

99
00:05:15.379 --> 00:05:17.022
Solid. not striped.

100
00:05:17.046 --> 00:05:18.650
I don't want you passing out on me now.

101
00:05:18.674 --> 00:05:20.304
Can we focus?

102
00:05:20.328 --> 00:05:22.437
A massive piece of intel
on a major terrorist

103
00:05:22.461 --> 00:05:24.091
just fell into our lap.

104
00:05:24.115 --> 00:05:26.006
Yeah. so. um. today I was approached by

105
00:05:26.030 --> 00:05:27.703
the wealth manager of the Levni Company.

106
00:05:27.727 --> 00:05:31.196
She's claiming that the family
are buying oil from Abdul Akkad.

107
00:05:31.220 --> 00:05:32.969
So I guess the question
we want to ask is.

108
00:05:32.993 --> 00:05:34.666
is that even possible?

109
00:05:34.690 --> 00:05:36.451
Do I seem shocked?

110
00:05:36.475 --> 00:05:39.454
Look. terrorists control
the oil fields in Syria.

111
00:05:39.478 --> 00:05:41.586
And U.S. sanctions
put a cork in it. but...

112
00:05:41.610 --> 00:05:43.588
But Al Sulam claimed
the attack on a merchant vessel

113
00:05:43.612 --> 00:05:46.765
- in the Mediterranean yesterday.
- Yeah. 41 Americans killed.

114
00:05:46.789 --> 00:05:49.594
They used long-range.
military-grade drones.

115
00:05:49.618 --> 00:05:53.033
So clearly they've figured some
way around these sanctions.

116
00:05:53.057 --> 00:05:54.773
Those drones ain't cheap.

117
00:05:54.797 --> 00:05:57.559
All right. so the Levni Company
gets cheap crude oil to refine.

118
00:05:57.583 --> 00:06:00.344
and Al Sulam gets money to
finance their war against the West.

119
00:06:00.368 --> 00:06:01.606
Abdul's been on our radar for years.

120
00:06:01.630 --> 00:06:03.521
We just haven't been able
to pin down his location.

121
00:06:03.545 --> 00:06:05.523
Well. the good news is. the Levni family

122
00:06:05.547 --> 00:06:08.439
are all in town this weekend
for a family wedding.

123
00:06:08.463 --> 00:06:11.529
and I can get us in there.
The rehearsal dinner's today.

124
00:06:11.553 --> 00:06:13.749
We need an asset
inside the Levni family.

125
00:06:13.773 --> 00:06:16.317
someone with access.
someone closer to Abdul.

126
00:06:16.341 --> 00:06:17.361
Well. if you guys can figure out

127
00:06:17.385 --> 00:06:20.103
where Abdul's been operating out of.

128
00:06:20.127 --> 00:06:21.583
then we can take care of the rest.

129
00:06:21.607 --> 00:06:22.758
- On it.
- OK.

130
00:06:22.782 --> 00:06:24.281
OK. Thanks. Larry.

131
00:06:24.305 --> 00:06:25.804
Bill. you'll be there too.

132
00:06:25.828 --> 00:06:28.242
Try to blend in with security detail.

133
00:06:28.266 --> 00:06:30.548
What. so Bill's going
undercover as Bill?

134
00:06:30.572 --> 00:06:33.334
You'd be surprised what
I can glean from the sidelines.

135
00:06:36.404 --> 00:06:39.339
Let me get my glad rags on.

136
00:07:02.256 --> 00:07:03.886
Who died?

137
00:07:03.910 --> 00:07:05.366
I'm on my way to a rehearsal dinner.

138
00:07:05.390 --> 00:07:07.977
- thank you very much.
- Need a date?

139
00:07:08.001 --> 00:07:10.893
Not this time.
but I'll bear you in mind.

140
00:07:10.917 --> 00:07:13.461
So where are we at
with our little project?

141
00:07:13.485 --> 00:07:15.245
I checked the firewall
structure you sent over.

142
00:07:15.269 --> 00:07:16.986
It's doable. this breach.

143
00:07:17.010 --> 00:07:18.553
I'll be able to program a device.

144
00:07:18.577 --> 00:07:20.250
All you have to do is plug it in.

145
00:07:20.274 --> 00:07:22.252
It'll download all the files in seconds.

146
00:07:22.276 --> 00:07:24.298
No one will ever know
you were on their server.

147
00:07:24.322 --> 00:07:26.471
Excellent. What's the time frame?

148
00:07:30.110 --> 00:07:32.306
- Give me a week.
- A week?

149
00:07:32.330 --> 00:07:34.308
How about a couple of days?

150
00:07:34.332 --> 00:07:35.918
Oh. come on. Kinski. you're the best.

151
00:07:35.942 --> 00:07:37.615
There's no team.

152
00:07:37.639 --> 00:07:39.443
I'm a one-woman shop.
and I have other clients.

153
00:07:39.467 --> 00:07:41.097
I have money.

154
00:07:41.121 --> 00:07:42.968
You work through the night.
I'll make it worth your while.

155
00:07:47.475 --> 00:07:50.324
- I'll have it ready by Monday.
- Good.

156
00:07:50.348 --> 00:07:52.369
Well. if this works out.
I'll give you a 5-star review.

157
00:07:52.393 --> 00:07:54.676
I prefer word of mouth.

158
00:07:54.700 --> 00:07:56.881
Who are these people. anyway?

159
00:07:56.905 --> 00:07:58.680
For your safety.
the less you know. the better.

160
00:08:02.055 --> 00:08:04.425
What's your dream wedding?

161
00:08:04.449 --> 00:08:05.600
Oh. to elope.

162
00:08:05.624 --> 00:08:07.428
Excuse me.

163
00:08:07.452 --> 00:08:08.559
Thanks.

164
00:08:11.499 --> 00:08:14.478
Come on. all the money in the world.

165
00:08:14.502 --> 00:08:16.262
and you'd run to the courthouse?

166
00:08:16.286 --> 00:08:18.134
Well. a destination courthouse.

167
00:08:18.158 --> 00:08:20.354
- South of France.
- I knew it.

168
00:08:20.378 --> 00:08:22.051
You are a romantic.

169
00:08:23.511 --> 00:08:24.880
So come on then. fill me in.

170
00:08:24.904 --> 00:08:26.323
Mm.

171
00:08:27.863 --> 00:08:30.233
That is Nasir.

172
00:08:30.257 --> 00:08:32.496
acting CEO of Levni Co.

173
00:08:32.520 --> 00:08:34.977
My guess. he's running the oil trade.

174
00:08:35.001 --> 00:08:36.674
Ever since he took over from his father.

175
00:08:36.698 --> 00:08:38.589
profits have gone up 200%.

176
00:08:38.613 --> 00:08:41.287
Well. he seems quite calm for
a man in bed with terrorists.

177
00:08:41.311 --> 00:08:43.333
He's impossible to read.

178
00:08:43.357 --> 00:08:44.856
Controlled.

179
00:08:44.880 --> 00:08:46.423
So. boring then.

180
00:08:46.447 --> 00:08:48.947
If you fancy better company.

181
00:08:48.971 --> 00:08:50.645
try the bride-to-be.

182
00:08:50.669 --> 00:08:54.039
Selma Levni and her fiancé. Ali.

183
00:08:54.063 --> 00:08:58.087
He's an environmental lawyer.
she is a clean energy activist.

184
00:08:58.111 --> 00:09:01.873
and together. they run
Levni Co's Green Energy branch.

185
00:09:01.897 --> 00:09:03.962
Well. there's an oxymoron.
if ever I heard one.

186
00:09:03.986 --> 00:09:07.009
What about the youngest?

187
00:09:07.033 --> 00:09:08.924
Kerem.

188
00:09:08.948 --> 00:09:11.579
To my far left at the end of the bar.

189
00:09:11.603 --> 00:09:14.582
he's head of special
projects at Levni Co.

190
00:09:14.606 --> 00:09:17.324
- Ah. the black sheep.
- The free spirit.

191
00:09:17.348 --> 00:09:19.239
He's not dumb.

192
00:09:19.263 --> 00:09:22.198
But he'd get a lot more traction
if he could control the drinking

193
00:09:22.222 --> 00:09:24.461
and the drugs and a dozen other things.

194
00:09:24.485 --> 00:09:26.028
Fun.

195
00:09:26.052 --> 00:09:28.468
Well. seems like we've got
the best shot of turning Kerem.

196
00:09:30.143 --> 00:09:32.687
Kerem. Hello.

197
00:09:32.711 --> 00:09:35.994
Ah. Zara. hello.

198
00:09:36.018 --> 00:09:37.561
- You look fantastic.
- Oh.

199
00:09:37.585 --> 00:09:39.911
I want you to meet Phil.

200
00:09:39.935 --> 00:09:41.173
- Hey. man. How are you?
- Hi.

201
00:09:41.197 --> 00:09:42.653
- Nice to meet you.
- Phil.

202
00:09:42.677 --> 00:09:45.352
I run a mid-tech VC fund
at Pollard-Heyer.

203
00:09:45.376 --> 00:09:47.049
and. uh. well. Zara was just telling me

204
00:09:47.073 --> 00:09:48.224
here about your latest placement.

205
00:09:48.248 --> 00:09:50.052
It's impressive. man.
How'd you find 'em?

206
00:09:50.076 --> 00:09:52.359
Well. Zara. you're
embarrassing me. first of all.

207
00:09:54.994 --> 00:09:56.580
Everything OK?

208
00:09:56.604 --> 00:09:58.626
I figured... if you're going to be up

209
00:09:58.650 --> 00:10:00.715
on your feet all night.
you deserve some fuel.

210
00:10:00.739 --> 00:10:02.847
Even security guards need to eat.

211
00:10:02.871 --> 00:10:04.980
Oh. that's very thoughtful. Thank you.

212
00:10:05.004 --> 00:10:07.112
I have a rule. No eating while on duty.

213
00:10:07.136 --> 00:10:08.508
Oh.

214
00:10:09.487 --> 00:10:11.987
I thought we were going
to have a small wedding.

215
00:10:12.011 --> 00:10:16.208
and then Ali decided to fly
in a chef from Turkey. so...

216
00:10:16.232 --> 00:10:18.080
My fiancée is the same.

217
00:10:18.104 --> 00:10:19.299
Said she wanted modest.

218
00:10:19.323 --> 00:10:21.388
now we're talking floral arches...

219
00:10:21.412 --> 00:10:23.041
plural.

220
00:10:23.065 --> 00:10:24.521
- Here you go.
- Oh. thanks.

221
00:10:24.545 --> 00:10:26.262
- Hi. I'm Ali.
- Bill.

222
00:10:26.286 --> 00:10:27.611
Enjoying the food?

223
00:10:27.635 --> 00:10:29.831
- I flew in the most...
- Oh. he heard. He heard.

224
00:10:29.855 --> 00:10:31.659
- And?
- Oh. I haven't tried it yet.

225
00:10:31.683 --> 00:10:33.400
I will be taking a doggy bag
on the way home. though.

226
00:10:33.424 --> 00:10:34.784
It smells delicious.

227
00:10:38.254 --> 00:10:41.103
Hello. Thank you for coming.

228
00:10:41.127 --> 00:10:44.845
I'm Nasir. Selma's brother.

229
00:10:44.869 --> 00:10:47.239
I wish our father could be here
to welcome you all.

230
00:10:47.263 --> 00:10:49.633
but we all pray for his swift recovery.

231
00:10:49.657 --> 00:10:52.854
Selma has always been
the heart of our family.

232
00:10:52.878 --> 00:10:55.770
And when she met Ali. I was...

233
00:10:55.794 --> 00:10:58.642
Protective.

234
00:10:58.666 --> 00:11:01.732
This last month. it hasn't been easy.

235
00:11:01.756 --> 00:11:03.995
But you've been there for me
through all of it.

236
00:11:04.397 --> 00:11:05.815
Thank you.

237
00:11:08.902 --> 00:11:10.872
A cheers to the happy couple.

238
00:11:10.896 --> 00:11:13.048
Cheers.

239
00:11:26.694 --> 00:11:27.715
Nasir!

240
00:11:27.739 --> 00:11:29.238
Nasir! Help! Help!

241
00:11:29.262 --> 00:11:31.066
- Somebody call 911!
- Get him up.

242
00:11:31.090 --> 00:11:32.894
Nasir. can you hear me?

243
00:11:32.918 --> 00:11:34.069
Stop!

244
00:11:51.632 --> 00:11:54.306
I didn't know! I didn't know!

245
00:11:54.330 --> 00:11:55.740
Yeah. we'll be the judge of that.

246
00:12:00.206 --> 00:12:01.792
So you believe his story?

247
00:12:01.816 --> 00:12:03.794
What. that someone hired him. a caterer.

248
00:12:03.818 --> 00:12:06.493
to deliver a glass of champagne
to the most important man

249
00:12:06.517 --> 00:12:07.929
in the room with no explanation?

250
00:12:07.953 --> 00:12:09.147
No. I don't.

251
00:12:09.171 --> 00:12:11.933
Yeah. he knew what he
was doing and that was a hit.

252
00:12:11.957 --> 00:12:13.978
But I'd buy he doesn't know
who hired him.

253
00:12:16.744 --> 00:12:19.486
Hey. guys. come here for a second.

254
00:12:25.632 --> 00:12:27.272
Nasir is dead.

255
00:12:27.929 --> 00:12:29.951
The tox report came back
with high concentrations

256
00:12:29.975 --> 00:12:32.944
of cyanide in his blood.
The killer took no chances.

257
00:12:33.587 --> 00:12:35.957
So the caterer seems
to be an assassin for hire.

258
00:12:35.981 --> 00:12:38.525
Question now is.
who wanted Nasir off the board?

259
00:12:38.549 --> 00:12:40.962
If Nasir was working with Abdul Akkad.

260
00:12:40.986 --> 00:12:43.399
maybe their deal went south.
This could be payback.

261
00:12:43.423 --> 00:12:45.183
Or it could be a power play.

262
00:12:45.207 --> 00:12:48.012
I mean. with Nasir out of the way.
the CEO spot opens up.

263
00:12:48.036 --> 00:12:49.884
Whoever it is. the best course of action

264
00:12:49.908 --> 00:12:51.799
is still getting an asset
inside the family.

265
00:12:51.823 --> 00:12:54.323
We need more intel on how
Al Sulam is circumventing

266
00:12:54.347 --> 00:12:56.020
those oil sanctions.

267
00:12:56.044 --> 00:12:59.328
- Colin. you work Kerem.
- On it.

268
00:12:59.352 --> 00:13:00.808
Bill. you take on the newlyweds.

269
00:13:00.832 --> 00:13:03.114
They're in mourning.
I'll go pay my respects.

270
00:13:04.749 --> 00:13:06.770
Bill. your first recruitment job.

271
00:13:06.794 --> 00:13:08.642
Should we take a photo?
Remember the moment?

272
00:13:15.832 --> 00:13:17.477
Kerem.

273
00:13:17.501 --> 00:13:19.783
Oh. easy. fellas.

274
00:13:19.807 --> 00:13:22.003
He's cool. Let him through.

275
00:13:27.423 --> 00:13:29.227
Can't blame them
for being jumpy. I suppose.

276
00:13:29.251 --> 00:13:31.926
Right. Uh. you want coffee?

277
00:13:31.950 --> 00:13:34.102
Please.

278
00:13:40.175 --> 00:13:41.762
Thank you.

279
00:13:43.048 --> 00:13:44.720
I'm. uh...

280
00:13:44.744 --> 00:13:46.810
I'm so sorry about your brother.

281
00:13:46.834 --> 00:13:48.246
Crazy thing to happen.

282
00:13:49.593 --> 00:13:51.293
Yes. not the best speech.

283
00:13:54.886 --> 00:13:56.690
I thought you'd be drinking something

284
00:13:56.714 --> 00:13:57.908
a little more stronger. to be honest.

285
00:14:00.326 --> 00:14:02.957
What do you normally do
to blow off steam?

286
00:14:07.899 --> 00:14:09.137
You drive stick shift?

287
00:14:55.381 --> 00:14:57.925
Whoa.

288
00:14:57.949 --> 00:15:00.841
- I needed that.
- Yeah. me too. it turns out.

289
00:15:00.865 --> 00:15:02.799
I'm sorry about that last corner.

290
00:15:02.823 --> 00:15:04.671
- I don't know what came over me.
- Uh-huh.

291
00:15:06.886 --> 00:15:09.197
Here's to grieving. eh?

292
00:15:11.092 --> 00:15:12.833
Yeah.

293
00:15:15.836 --> 00:15:18.901
Oh. this is gonna destroy my sister.

294
00:15:20.362 --> 00:15:22.514
Let me tell you something
about my brother.

295
00:15:22.538 --> 00:15:24.473
I hated him growing up.

296
00:15:24.497 --> 00:15:26.344
Everything was a competition.

297
00:15:26.368 --> 00:15:28.869
and our father played into it too.

298
00:15:28.893 --> 00:15:30.914
Look... look what...
look what Nasir has.

299
00:15:30.938 --> 00:15:32.394
Look what Nasir did.

300
00:15:32.418 --> 00:15:35.484
Well. don't try too hard.

301
00:15:35.508 --> 00:15:37.617
Adulthood is overrated.

302
00:15:37.641 --> 00:15:41.359
- You got siblings?
- Yeah. older sister.

303
00:15:41.383 --> 00:15:44.986
She. uh. graduated
top of her class at Oxford.

304
00:15:45.011 --> 00:15:47.686
Now she's a world-renowned
doctor with four kids.

305
00:15:47.738 --> 00:15:49.890
Training for another marathon.

306
00:15:49.914 --> 00:15:53.284
You know. I got into
investing to make a mark.

307
00:15:53.308 --> 00:15:55.112
to find my own way.

308
00:15:55.136 --> 00:15:58.942
and they just think
it's some selfish thing.

309
00:15:58.966 --> 00:16:01.641
Kerem. do you. um... do you mind

310
00:16:01.665 --> 00:16:03.446
if we have a little bit of privacy.

311
00:16:12.937 --> 00:16:15.089
Listen. I wouldn't
normally work this fast.

312
00:16:15.113 --> 00:16:18.745
but time's against us.
and. well. to be honest.

313
00:16:18.769 --> 00:16:20.964
you're exactly what
I've been looking for.

314
00:16:20.988 --> 00:16:23.966
You know. a bold thinker. a risk-taker.

315
00:16:25.166 --> 00:16:27.014
I think you've got a lot
of good ideas. Kerem.

316
00:16:27.038 --> 00:16:28.580
but I'm not an investor.

317
00:16:28.604 --> 00:16:30.321
So what are you talking about?

318
00:16:31.956 --> 00:16:34.456
I'm a CIA operative.

319
00:16:34.480 --> 00:16:36.327
and I want you to work with me.

320
00:16:40.442 --> 00:16:42.856
Ali. can you help me out here?

321
00:16:42.880 --> 00:16:45.772
We have to bring the body home now.

322
00:16:45.796 --> 00:16:48.339
Do you understand that
my brother was just murdered?

323
00:16:48.363 --> 00:16:49.732
I respect how difficult this is.

324
00:16:49.756 --> 00:16:51.429
This is the opposite of respect.

325
00:16:51.453 --> 00:16:52.866
Excuse me.

326
00:16:52.890 --> 00:16:55.782
Special Agent Goodman. FBI.
What seems to be the problem?

327
00:16:55.806 --> 00:16:57.044
You're the guy from the rehearsal.

328
00:16:57.068 --> 00:16:59.873
- You took down Nasir's killer.
- Yes. I did.

329
00:16:59.897 --> 00:17:01.483
They won't let us take Nasir home.

330
00:17:01.507 --> 00:17:04.791
An Islamic burial has
to happen within 24 hours.

331
00:17:04.815 --> 00:17:06.426
Detective. a word?

332
00:17:11.647 --> 00:17:12.929
The killer's in custody.

333
00:17:12.953 --> 00:17:14.496
The medical examiner
completed the autopsy.

334
00:17:14.520 --> 00:17:16.150
Let the family make their arrangements.

335
00:17:16.174 --> 00:17:17.281
Mr. Levni's death is still
an active murder investigation.

336
00:17:17.305 --> 00:17:18.565
Oh. come on.

337
00:17:18.589 --> 00:17:19.821
What. you can't reach out
to your people?

338
00:17:19.845 --> 00:17:21.938
Agent Goodman. my hands
are tied on the matter.

339
00:17:21.962 --> 00:17:24.193
- Excuse me.
- Yeah. thanks for nothing.

340
00:17:27.793 --> 00:17:29.449
I'm sorry about that.

341
00:17:29.715 --> 00:17:32.781
And I'm especially sorry for your loss.

342
00:17:32.973 --> 00:17:34.995
Thank you.

343
00:17:36.237 --> 00:17:38.689
Uh. any leads as to
who hired the killer?

344
00:17:38.713 --> 00:17:40.478
Not yet.

345
00:17:40.502 --> 00:17:42.742
And I'm sure this has been exhausting.

346
00:17:42.766 --> 00:17:44.768
but is there any more
information you can share?

347
00:17:47.379 --> 00:17:50.314
Selma. it's OK.

348
00:17:50.338 --> 00:17:52.180
You can tell him.

349
00:18:02.263 --> 00:18:03.937
When Nasir took over.

350
00:18:03.961 --> 00:18:07.244
he inherited Levni Co's money problems.

351
00:18:07.268 --> 00:18:09.681
the kind that could have ruined us.

352
00:18:09.705 --> 00:18:12.283
He was desperate to keep us afloat.

353
00:18:13.100 --> 00:18:15.992
so he made some deals
with some shady people.

354
00:18:16.016 --> 00:18:17.428
Do you know these shady people?

355
00:18:17.452 --> 00:18:18.821
He wouldn't say.

356
00:18:18.845 --> 00:18:20.867
Didn't want to drag me into it.

357
00:18:20.891 --> 00:18:23.478
I mean. he didn't even admit
to it until a week ago.

358
00:18:23.502 --> 00:18:26.089
He just told me that
he wanted out of the deal

359
00:18:26.113 --> 00:18:28.309
and that he was scared of retaliation.

360
00:18:28.333 --> 00:18:31.360
She encouraged him to follow through.
to cut things off.

361
00:18:31.384 --> 00:18:33.749
You did the right thing. baby.

362
00:18:33.773 --> 00:18:35.229
Sure doesn't feel like it.

363
00:18:35.253 --> 00:18:37.318
Well. you did what you thought was best.

364
00:18:37.342 --> 00:18:40.234
And believe me. we will
find out who's behind this.

365
00:18:40.258 --> 00:18:41.931
You know. moving forward. I think

366
00:18:41.955 --> 00:18:44.368
if we work together. form a partnership.

367
00:18:44.392 --> 00:18:45.892
we could keep you and your company safe.

368
00:18:45.916 --> 00:18:49.852
I'm sorry. I can't do this right now.

369
00:18:49.876 --> 00:18:51.549
I completely understand.

370
00:18:51.573 --> 00:18:53.551
Take all the time you need.

371
00:18:53.575 --> 00:18:55.249
If you need anything. don't hesitate.

372
00:18:55.273 --> 00:18:57.120
All right.

373
00:18:59.494 --> 00:19:02.822
So my brother was buying oil
from Syrian terrorists?

374
00:19:02.846 --> 00:19:04.998
And that's who we think killed him.

375
00:19:05.022 --> 00:19:08.175
And who knows who else
they're gonna go after.

376
00:19:08.199 --> 00:19:11.439
Kerem. with your help. we can stop them.

377
00:19:11.463 --> 00:19:13.049
We can find their leader.

378
00:19:13.073 --> 00:19:15.617
and we can keep the rest
of your family safe.

379
00:19:15.641 --> 00:19:17.765
We can keep Selma safe.

380
00:19:19.079 --> 00:19:22.145
Look. I get it. This is a big decision.

381
00:19:22.169 --> 00:19:24.272
So why don't you. um...

382
00:19:24.780 --> 00:19:26.367
why don't you have a think about it?

383
00:19:26.391 --> 00:19:29.860
And if you're on board.
you call me on this number...

384
00:19:30.656 --> 00:19:32.634
and you order a burger.

385
00:19:32.658 --> 00:19:34.418
A what? A burger?

386
00:19:34.442 --> 00:19:37.493
Fully dressed. no tomato.
with a side of fries.

387
00:19:38.403 --> 00:19:41.289
What if I'm not. um. hungry?

388
00:19:42.059 --> 00:19:46.502
Kerem. I see how people
underestimate you in your life.

389
00:19:47.020 --> 00:19:50.850
but I know that you would be
a great addition to my team.

390
00:19:54.549 --> 00:19:56.470
Speak soon.

391
00:19:56.812 --> 00:19:58.616
Kerem seems game on the asset front.

392
00:19:58.640 --> 00:20:00.053
I think I can get him there.

393
00:20:00.077 --> 00:20:01.793
Well. Selma and Ali are
gonna take a little more time.

394
00:20:01.817 --> 00:20:04.318
but both claim Nasir
was dirty and wanted out.

395
00:20:04.342 --> 00:20:06.624
So it's plausible Al Sulam killed him.

396
00:20:06.648 --> 00:20:07.843
You don't kill your inside man

397
00:20:07.867 --> 00:20:09.149
unless you had a backup plan.

398
00:20:09.173 --> 00:20:11.064
There must be someone else.

399
00:20:11.088 --> 00:20:13.066
Hey. so I've been looking at the family

400
00:20:13.090 --> 00:20:14.981
financials that Zara sent over.

401
00:20:15.005 --> 00:20:18.158
We know that Nasir's killer
was paid $47.000.

402
00:20:18.182 --> 00:20:20.421
which is 2.1 million Turkish lira.

403
00:20:20.445 --> 00:20:23.511
But guess who just
converted that exact amount

404
00:20:23.535 --> 00:20:27.418
- to crypto two weeks ago?
- Kerem.

405
00:20:27.887 --> 00:20:30.474
Damn. I told him I was CIA.

406
00:20:30.498 --> 00:20:32.215
He's probably on the run as we speak.

407
00:20:32.239 --> 00:20:34.565
We gotta move now. You got his location?

408
00:20:38.158 --> 00:20:39.847
Hello?

409
00:20:41.031 --> 00:20:43.444
Yes. I can place that for you.

410
00:20:43.468 --> 00:20:45.227
Please hold.

411
00:20:45.731 --> 00:20:48.405
Kerem's on the line. ordering a burger.

412
00:20:48.429 --> 00:20:50.364
fully dressed. no tomato. side of fries.

413
00:20:50.388 --> 00:20:52.018
Meaning?

414
00:20:52.042 --> 00:20:53.584
Meaning he wants to be an asset

415
00:20:53.608 --> 00:20:55.696
or pretend to be one.

416
00:20:59.593 --> 00:21:01.435
OK. so Kerem is working for Al Sulam.

417
00:21:01.459 --> 00:21:03.159
paid to have his brother killed.

418
00:21:03.183 --> 00:21:05.031
and now he wants to be a CIA asset.

419
00:21:05.055 --> 00:21:06.423
Why?

420
00:21:06.447 --> 00:21:08.295
Well. maybe he wants something from us.

421
00:21:08.319 --> 00:21:11.863
Or maybe he's buying time.
trying to throw us off.

422
00:21:11.887 --> 00:21:14.924
- Or maybe it's a trap.
- Also a possibility.

423
00:21:15.630 --> 00:21:17.826
OK. so I...

424
00:21:17.850 --> 00:21:19.393
I distract Kerem with Spycraft 101

425
00:21:19.417 --> 00:21:20.655
while you clone his phone.
and then we just hope

426
00:21:20.679 --> 00:21:22.874
- that he's not setting us up.
- Yeah.

427
00:21:22.898 --> 00:21:24.180
If Kerem is working with Al Sulam.

428
00:21:24.204 --> 00:21:26.617
then hopefully we'll find
proof on his phone.

429
00:21:26.641 --> 00:21:28.619
Best case. it leads us
straight to Abdul Akkad.

430
00:21:28.643 --> 00:21:30.189
And worst case?

431
00:21:30.732 --> 00:21:34.538
- You react accordingly.
- Like...

432
00:21:35.541 --> 00:21:37.585
No. you just keep your cool.

433
00:21:37.609 --> 00:21:39.630
Don't give him time to think.
You'll be just fine.

434
00:21:39.654 --> 00:21:40.849
- OK?
- Yeah.

435
00:21:40.873 --> 00:21:42.633
OK.

436
00:21:49.447 --> 00:21:51.468
Is that bad?

437
00:21:51.492 --> 00:21:52.774
Is the beeping good or...

438
00:21:52.798 --> 00:21:54.384
It's completely normal.

439
00:21:54.408 --> 00:21:55.951
You know. my guys did this yesterday.

440
00:21:55.975 --> 00:21:58.160
so if there's any listening devices.
they would have found them.

441
00:21:58.184 --> 00:22:00.175
Your security team.
they work for the company?

442
00:22:00.199 --> 00:22:02.784
Yeah. which is why
you're doing this now.

443
00:22:02.808 --> 00:22:04.960
because they might
have been compromised?

444
00:22:04.984 --> 00:22:06.744
You're a fast learner. mate.

445
00:22:06.768 --> 00:22:08.964
So when we've finished this bug sweep.

446
00:22:08.988 --> 00:22:10.574
my colleague here
will teach you everything

447
00:22:10.598 --> 00:22:12.663
you need to know about
being a CIA asset.

448
00:22:12.687 --> 00:22:13.751
Should I be writing this down?

449
00:22:13.775 --> 00:22:15.362
You should stop drinking.

450
00:22:15.386 --> 00:22:17.233
And when did you join the agency?

451
00:22:17.257 --> 00:22:19.757
And for your first lesson.
we don't write anything down...

452
00:22:19.781 --> 00:22:21.455
- ever.
- And one more thing.

453
00:22:21.479 --> 00:22:24.762
- I need your phone.
- What? Why?

454
00:22:24.786 --> 00:22:27.461
Oh. the shopping apps.
they're listening too.

455
00:22:27.485 --> 00:22:28.853
So the Faraday enclosure
blocks all signals.

456
00:22:28.877 --> 00:22:30.203
But I...

457
00:22:30.227 --> 00:22:31.639
Trust me. mate. you won't be bored.

458
00:22:31.663 --> 00:22:33.380
- OK.
- Yeah.

459
00:22:33.404 --> 00:22:36.252
All right. so let's go over
routines and patterns.

460
00:22:36.276 --> 00:22:37.993
I'd love to know what you eat regularly.

461
00:22:38.017 --> 00:22:39.777
places you go. people you see.

462
00:22:39.801 --> 00:22:41.518
all these details are very important.

463
00:22:41.542 --> 00:22:44.136
Uh. I go to the office most days.

464
00:22:44.160 --> 00:22:45.566
Great.

465
00:22:45.590 --> 00:22:47.350
And. um. I've been flying
back and forth to Istanbul

466
00:22:47.374 --> 00:22:50.179
to see my father. but. uh... the gym.

467
00:22:50.203 --> 00:22:51.920
I'm at the gym. like. Monday. Tuesday.

468
00:22:51.944 --> 00:22:53.313
Tuesday is leg day.

469
00:22:53.337 --> 00:22:55.141
It's really important that you keep up

470
00:22:55.165 --> 00:22:56.968
these routines so you don't
raise any suspicion.

471
00:22:56.992 --> 00:22:59.145
OK. No. no. I mean.
that's just to start.

472
00:22:59.169 --> 00:23:00.494
But then I'll rest Wednesday.

473
00:23:00.518 --> 00:23:01.886
and then mostly
I'll spend time with the...

474
00:23:01.910 --> 00:23:03.018
OK. And weekends?

475
00:23:03.042 --> 00:23:04.846
What about hobbies?

476
00:23:09.396 --> 00:23:12.201
- Sarah?
- Oh. thank God.

477
00:23:12.225 --> 00:23:14.160
Pyramid is rolling out this new OS.

478
00:23:14.184 --> 00:23:16.423
and it's wiped half my phone.

479
00:23:16.447 --> 00:23:18.729
I've been trying to call Paul.
but he's not picking up.

480
00:23:18.753 --> 00:23:20.427
OK. OK. OK.

481
00:23:20.451 --> 00:23:22.429
- What's going on?
- Well. it's Max.

482
00:23:22.453 --> 00:23:25.171
His karate class ended and.
um... and Paul was supposed

483
00:23:25.195 --> 00:23:26.650
to pick him up. but he never showed.

484
00:23:26.674 --> 00:23:29.914
And now he's alone in a lobby.
and I'm 45 minutes away.

485
00:23:29.938 --> 00:23:31.133
Well. what's the address?

486
00:23:31.157 --> 00:23:35.268
It's um... it's 724 West 57th.

487
00:23:35.292 --> 00:23:37.764
Well. I can be there in 15 minutes.
I'll wait with him.

488
00:23:37.788 --> 00:23:40.229
OK. thank you. Thank you.

489
00:23:40.253 --> 00:23:41.839
I'm... I'm on my way.

490
00:23:41.863 --> 00:23:44.059
- I'll be there as fast as I can.
- No problem. honestly.

491
00:23:44.083 --> 00:23:45.908
- Thank you.
- OK. bye.

492
00:23:51.482 --> 00:23:54.374
- What's up?
- Kinski. change of plan.

493
00:23:54.398 --> 00:23:55.810
They've started upgrading the firewall.

494
00:23:55.834 --> 00:23:57.503
I need that device tonight.

495
00:23:58.445 --> 00:24:01.032
Zeeb. you finish sorting
through Kerem's phone?

496
00:24:01.056 --> 00:24:02.329
Anything damning?

497
00:24:02.353 --> 00:24:04.247
I think so. Come take a look at this.

498
00:24:04.271 --> 00:24:06.386
There are several emails
and texts pertaining

499
00:24:06.410 --> 00:24:09.389
to crypto transfers from a Ramzi Fayez.

500
00:24:09.413 --> 00:24:10.868
who's an art dealer.

501
00:24:10.892 --> 00:24:12.827
Syrian national based here in New York.

502
00:24:12.851 --> 00:24:14.655
So Kerem paid for
the hit on his brother.

503
00:24:14.679 --> 00:24:18.441
- These are our receipts?
- Well. yes and no.

504
00:24:18.465 --> 00:24:19.921
I mean. technically. it is a receipt.

505
00:24:19.945 --> 00:24:22.097
but it's for a Mesopotamian orthostat.

506
00:24:22.121 --> 00:24:23.881
It's a 3.000-year-old slab of marble

507
00:24:23.905 --> 00:24:25.579
from the Palace of Nimrud.

508
00:24:25.603 --> 00:24:27.363
You know. 47K seems cheap

509
00:24:27.387 --> 00:24:28.930
considering the cultural significance.

510
00:24:28.954 --> 00:24:31.799
Well. that's because he's not buying it.
Zeeb. It's a front.

511
00:24:31.823 --> 00:24:34.979
Kerem pays for rare antiques in crypto.

512
00:24:35.003 --> 00:24:37.484
and then Ramzi uses that
to hire out a hit on Nasir.

513
00:24:37.508 --> 00:24:39.257
Well. do you want me to send
the address to Colin?

514
00:24:39.281 --> 00:24:42.552
No. he's busy.
He said he's meeting with a source.

515
00:24:42.576 --> 00:24:45.251
But you know what? Send it to Bill.

516
00:24:45.275 --> 00:24:46.861
Tell him to ruffle some feathers. huh?

517
00:24:48.833 --> 00:24:50.299
OK.

518
00:24:50.323 --> 00:24:51.779
This should be good.

519
00:25:05.338 --> 00:25:07.011
Come on. pick up.

520
00:25:07.035 --> 00:25:09.057
Pick up.

521
00:25:16.306 --> 00:25:18.458
- Hello?
- Hello. Good afternoon.

522
00:25:18.482 --> 00:25:21.243
- I'm calling for Ramzi.
- Yeah. this is he.

523
00:25:21.267 --> 00:25:24.420
Fantastic. Ramzi. I'm looking to acquire

524
00:25:24.444 --> 00:25:26.727
an Assyrian antiquity for my collection.

525
00:25:26.751 --> 00:25:28.598
Well. you called the wrong place.

526
00:25:28.622 --> 00:25:31.122
- This is a modern gallery.
- Well. I heard otherwise.

527
00:25:31.146 --> 00:25:33.386
I was told you are
the best at rare finds.

528
00:25:33.410 --> 00:25:34.691
Highly adept.

529
00:25:34.715 --> 00:25:36.780
Well. you've been misinformed.

530
00:25:36.804 --> 00:25:38.434
I'm sorry. Who is this?

531
00:25:38.458 --> 00:25:41.176
I'm a dear friend of
our mutual acquaintance.

532
00:25:41.200 --> 00:25:42.743
Kerem Levni.

533
00:25:45.726 --> 00:25:49.402
Well. as I said. I don't
know anybody by that name.

534
00:25:49.426 --> 00:25:51.230
Well. this is a waste of my time.

535
00:25:51.254 --> 00:25:52.622
I need to call Kerem.

536
00:25:52.646 --> 00:25:54.798
OK. Do it. Good luck.

537
00:26:12.057 --> 00:26:13.513
Where the hell have you been?

538
00:26:13.537 --> 00:26:14.948
Something came up.

539
00:26:16.017 --> 00:26:17.691
Yeah. well.
I've been tailing an art dealer

540
00:26:17.715 --> 00:26:19.736
- slash money launderer.
- What are you talking about?

541
00:26:19.760 --> 00:26:21.260
Yeah. keep up. Glass.

542
00:26:21.284 --> 00:26:24.175
Kerem paid this guy Ramzi
to hire out the hit on Nasir.

543
00:26:24.199 --> 00:26:26.787
Now Ramzi thinks Kerem
blabbed the whole scheme.

544
00:26:26.811 --> 00:26:29.442
- You shook the tree.
- Vigorously.

545
00:26:29.466 --> 00:26:32.227
Now I'm hoping Ramzi goes to
confront Kerem at his hotel.

546
00:26:32.251 --> 00:26:35.274
Oh. and by the way. Zeeb.
he hacked the hotel's smart TV.

547
00:26:35.298 --> 00:26:36.840
A confession on tape. I love it.

548
00:26:36.864 --> 00:26:38.277
What's your ETA?

549
00:26:38.301 --> 00:26:39.800
Well. if he's headed
to the hotel right now.

550
00:26:39.824 --> 00:26:41.584
you got 20 minutes to beat him there.

551
00:26:41.608 --> 00:26:43.673
Well. I've gotta get Gina out of there.

552
00:26:43.697 --> 00:26:46.023
- It's gonna be tight.
- Yeah. whose fault is that?

553
00:26:46.047 --> 00:26:47.503
Yeah. I said tight. not impossible.

554
00:26:47.527 --> 00:26:48.722
Send me a photo of this Ramzi guy.

555
00:26:54.578 --> 00:26:56.991
Anytime you leave the hotel room.
lock the bottom lock only...

556
00:26:58.451 --> 00:27:01.387
- You expecting someone?
- No.

557
00:27:09.810 --> 00:27:11.266
Hey.

558
00:27:11.290 --> 00:27:12.948
We've got company coming.

559
00:27:13.831 --> 00:27:16.288
Sorry. Kerem. duty calls.

560
00:27:16.405 --> 00:27:18.774
Training's over for the day. I'm afraid.

561
00:27:18.825 --> 00:27:21.761
Uh. last lesson of the day...
don't leave this anywhere. OK?

562
00:27:21.786 --> 00:27:24.155
No. I wouldn't.
I didn't like giving it to you.

563
00:27:24.259 --> 00:27:25.597
All right. Great job today.

564
00:27:25.621 --> 00:27:26.934
- Yeah.
- We'll be in touch.

565
00:27:26.958 --> 00:27:28.631
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

566
00:27:28.655 --> 00:27:30.807
Great.

567
00:27:39.492 --> 00:27:40.774
All right. what's going on?

568
00:27:40.798 --> 00:27:42.602
Bill just sent me this.

569
00:27:42.626 --> 00:27:44.560
It's the guy who sorted out
the assassin.

570
00:27:44.584 --> 00:27:46.325
He's on his way here now
to meet with Kerem.

571
00:27:50.982 --> 00:27:52.873
That's him.

572
00:28:11.002 --> 00:28:13.328
Mashallah.

573
00:28:17.269 --> 00:28:18.681
I need to call Zeeb.

574
00:28:18.705 --> 00:28:21.336
Get him to hack the TV in Room 3610.

575
00:28:21.360 --> 00:28:23.928
Kerem didn't kill Nasir. Ali did.

576
00:28:30.500 --> 00:28:32.653
A man called my shop today.

577
00:28:34.025 --> 00:28:36.482
He wanted to buy some antiquities.

578
00:28:40.118 --> 00:28:42.270
He used your brother-in-law's name.

579
00:28:42.294 --> 00:28:43.750
Kerem.

580
00:28:43.774 --> 00:28:45.541
I don't know anything about that.

581
00:28:45.906 --> 00:28:48.127
Any loose lips?

582
00:28:48.953 --> 00:28:51.148
A whispered mention to your bride?

583
00:28:51.172 --> 00:28:53.382
Not a word to anyone. I swear.

584
00:28:58.441 --> 00:29:01.515
Our people took a significant risk...

585
00:29:04.055 --> 00:29:05.894
clearing a path for you.

586
00:29:06.522 --> 00:29:08.674
It's only a matter of time
until your father-in-law

587
00:29:08.699 --> 00:29:13.157
sees you as the man
to succeed him as CEO.

588
00:29:13.281 --> 00:29:16.957
the company. all of it...

589
00:29:19.723 --> 00:29:22.571
As long as you remain vigilant.

590
00:29:26.207 --> 00:29:30.361
We'll arrange a jet
back to Istanbul today.

591
00:29:30.385 --> 00:29:32.059
Take your fiancée.

592
00:29:32.083 --> 00:29:34.365
Tell her the family office
arranged a private plane

593
00:29:34.389 --> 00:29:36.150
for safety reasons.

594
00:29:36.174 --> 00:29:37.934
She won't leave without Nasir's body.

595
00:29:37.958 --> 00:29:39.887
We'll make sure it's on the plane.

596
00:29:41.005 --> 00:29:44.375
Back in Turkey. take some time. lay low.

597
00:29:44.808 --> 00:29:46.685
Have an intimate ceremony.

598
00:29:47.359 --> 00:29:49.381
Isn't that what Selma always wanted?

599
00:29:49.579 --> 00:29:50.817
Well. we were half right.

600
00:29:50.841 --> 00:29:52.862
Al Sulam took out Nasir to replace him

601
00:29:52.886 --> 00:29:56.126
with a more willing puppet.
It just wasn't Kerem.

602
00:29:56.150 --> 00:29:58.651
- No. Kerem was the fall guy.
- We should have seen it.

603
00:29:58.675 --> 00:30:00.174
I mean. Ali's perfect. isn't he?

604
00:30:00.198 --> 00:30:02.829
Marrying up. ambitious. easy to control.

605
00:30:02.853 --> 00:30:04.308
He's a good asset.

606
00:30:04.332 --> 00:30:06.267
And now we have everything
we need to recruit him.

607
00:30:06.291 --> 00:30:08.878
Oh. come on. we're not really
gonna work with this guy.

608
00:30:08.902 --> 00:30:10.837
Well. what did you think we were doing?

609
00:30:10.861 --> 00:30:12.882
Solving a murder. then reduce
his sentence in exchange

610
00:30:12.906 --> 00:30:14.262
for Abdul's location.

611
00:30:14.286 --> 00:30:16.886
No. Bill. we're gonna play
the long game here.

612
00:30:16.910 --> 00:30:19.503
We'll get Abdul Akkad's location.
then we'll put Ali back in.

613
00:30:19.527 --> 00:30:21.021
We'll use him to make sure
the Levni Company

614
00:30:21.045 --> 00:30:22.683
never funds terrorism ever again.

615
00:30:22.707 --> 00:30:25.207
Ali conspired to murder
his own brother-in-law.

616
00:30:25.231 --> 00:30:26.251
We can't trust him.

617
00:30:26.275 --> 00:30:27.949
Trust. maybe not.

618
00:30:27.973 --> 00:30:30.671
But we can leverage it against
him for the rest of his life.

619
00:30:32.804 --> 00:30:35.391
Oh. Nikki. your call.
What do you want to do?

620
00:30:35.415 --> 00:30:37.903
Arrest Ali or recruit him?

621
00:30:38.766 --> 00:30:40.831
I think there's a third option.

622
00:30:46.165 --> 00:30:49.013
Ali. Selma. I am
your flight concierge. Jane.

623
00:30:49.037 --> 00:30:50.749
May I?

624
00:30:54.129 --> 00:30:56.151
And my brother's body?

625
00:30:56.175 --> 00:30:58.131
It's all taken care of.

626
00:30:58.917 --> 00:31:01.286
Told you. honey.
They've handled everything.

627
00:31:01.310 --> 00:31:02.897
We're gonna be OK.

628
00:31:05.402 --> 00:31:06.901
We'll get you through
without any hassle.

629
00:31:06.925 --> 00:31:08.903
Right this way.

630
00:31:11.320 --> 00:31:14.019
Almost there. yeah?

631
00:31:17.326 --> 00:31:19.479
Wait! Wait! Wait. wait. Selma!

632
00:31:19.503 --> 00:31:20.567
- Kerem?
- You have to wait!

633
00:31:20.591 --> 00:31:21.568
- What are you doing here?
- Wait.

634
00:31:21.592 --> 00:31:22.786
Uh. sir. excuse me. you can't be here.

635
00:31:22.810 --> 00:31:23.787
Just... just give me a second.
Just wait.

636
00:31:23.811 --> 00:31:25.528
OK. see her? She trained me. OK?

637
00:31:25.552 --> 00:31:27.225
- She's CIA.
- OK. all right.

638
00:31:27.249 --> 00:31:28.401
- Whatever you're on...
- Hold on a second.

639
00:31:28.425 --> 00:31:31.186
Just shut up for a second. OK? Please!

640
00:31:31.210 --> 00:31:34.058
The CIA is trying to control Levni Co.

641
00:31:34.082 --> 00:31:35.669
All right. they want to
turn me against the family.

642
00:31:35.693 --> 00:31:37.279
but I won't do it. I won't betray blood.

643
00:31:37.303 --> 00:31:38.541
I don't care about
the Syrian terrorists.

644
00:31:38.565 --> 00:31:40.238
- I don't care...
- Hey! Kerem. shut up.

645
00:31:40.262 --> 00:31:41.631
- Hey!
- Listen to me.

646
00:31:41.655 --> 00:31:42.719
We cannot get on this plane. please.

647
00:31:42.743 --> 00:31:44.217
- Stop it!
- We have to go right now.

648
00:31:44.241 --> 00:31:45.593
Hey! No. it's not! It's a trap!

649
00:31:45.617 --> 00:31:47.071
- Stop!
- Please

650
00:31:47.095 --> 00:31:48.551
- Kerem. you're scaring me.
- We have to leave right now.

651
00:31:48.575 --> 00:31:50.510
- You're scaring me.
- Get your hands off her! Let go of her!

652
00:31:50.534 --> 00:31:51.685
Let go of her and get out of here!

653
00:31:51.709 --> 00:31:53.077
- Hey. hey!
- What are you doing?

654
00:31:53.101 --> 00:31:55.355
OK. OK. Calm.

655
00:31:56.235 --> 00:31:58.126
Kerem's right. We are CIA.

656
00:31:58.150 --> 00:32:00.215
- What?
- What the hell is this?

657
00:32:00.239 --> 00:32:01.956
We're not here to arrest you. Ali.

658
00:32:01.980 --> 00:32:03.958
We want to make a deal.
so tell us what you know.

659
00:32:03.982 --> 00:32:05.786
Wait. wait. I don't understand.

660
00:32:05.810 --> 00:32:07.048
What... what does he know?

661
00:32:07.072 --> 00:32:09.050
- Ali. what do you know?
- I have no idea.

662
00:32:09.074 --> 00:32:11.574
Don't make this harder
than it needs to be.

663
00:32:11.598 --> 00:32:13.576
The CIA are full of liars.

664
00:32:13.600 --> 00:32:15.578
They're trained to do this. OK?

665
00:32:15.602 --> 00:32:17.275
Someone deserves to know. Just admit it.

666
00:32:17.299 --> 00:32:18.668
Admit what?

667
00:32:18.692 --> 00:32:20.235
We know you bought oil from Al Sulam.

668
00:32:20.259 --> 00:32:21.541
You ran it through the refinery.

669
00:32:21.565 --> 00:32:23.013
You're funding terrorism. Ali.

670
00:32:23.037 --> 00:32:24.848
- They're lying.
- We're not lying.

671
00:32:24.872 --> 00:32:26.117
- What's going on?
- Tell us the truth. Ali.

672
00:32:26.141 --> 00:32:28.286
- Come on.
- Everyone on the plane now!

673
00:32:28.310 --> 00:32:29.560
- Guys! Guys!
- Come on. come on. come on!

674
00:32:29.584 --> 00:32:30.941
Come on. Get on. guys.

675
00:32:30.965 --> 00:32:31.986
- Get on the plane.
- Let's go! Let's go! let's go!

676
00:32:32.010 --> 00:32:33.146
- Go!
- Hurry!

677
00:32:43.674 --> 00:32:46.391
OK. stay down.

678
00:32:51.159 --> 00:32:52.528
Kerem. were you followed?

679
00:32:52.552 --> 00:32:54.051
- By who?
- By Al Sulam.

680
00:32:54.075 --> 00:32:55.400
I don't know.

681
00:32:55.424 --> 00:32:57.054
This is why we told you
to stay at the hotel.

682
00:32:57.078 --> 00:32:58.186
You've led 'em right to us.

683
00:33:01.430 --> 00:33:03.998
Man down!

684
00:33:14.531 --> 00:33:15.856
I think I'm gonna be sick.

685
00:33:17.708 --> 00:33:19.686
Ali. Al Sulam is here
because of your mess.

686
00:33:19.710 --> 00:33:21.862
My guys are dying out there.
Now. you got two options...

687
00:33:21.886 --> 00:33:23.690
I throw you off this plane.
or you work with us.

688
00:33:23.714 --> 00:33:25.779
and we get this thing airborne.

689
00:33:26.543 --> 00:33:28.782
You have a chance to save
the woman you love.

690
00:33:28.806 --> 00:33:30.174
Take it.

691
00:33:36.074 --> 00:33:38.400
Listen. when Nasir got cold feet.

692
00:33:38.424 --> 00:33:41.098
they came to me. Al Sulam.

693
00:33:41.122 --> 00:33:42.317
What are you talking about?

694
00:33:42.341 --> 00:33:43.927
They just wanted
two more years of trade.

695
00:33:43.951 --> 00:33:47.235
In return. they'd help make me
CEO with you by my side.

696
00:33:49.130 --> 00:33:50.934
Baby. please. say something.

697
00:33:54.092 --> 00:33:56.476
Because of you. my brother is dead.

698
00:33:57.617 --> 00:33:59.552
Please. just get us out of here.

699
00:33:59.576 --> 00:34:00.847
I'll do it. I'll work with you.

700
00:34:00.871 --> 00:34:02.642
Just... we have to leave now!

701
00:34:02.666 --> 00:34:04.471
- You'll work with us?
- Yes!

702
00:34:04.495 --> 00:34:07.081
Yeah? Not necessary.

703
00:34:07.105 --> 00:34:09.605
Bill. call it.

704
00:34:09.629 --> 00:34:11.564
Hold your fire.

705
00:34:11.588 --> 00:34:12.913
At ease. boys!

706
00:34:15.156 --> 00:34:16.742
All right. you heard him!
Hold your fire.

707
00:34:16.766 --> 00:34:20.137
- Whoo!
- Kerem. you can come out now.

708
00:34:30.519 --> 00:34:31.932
No. it's not Al Sulam out there.

709
00:34:31.956 --> 00:34:33.628
That's our boys firing
blanks at each other.

710
00:34:33.652 --> 00:34:35.936
- No.
- You're under arrest.

711
00:34:53.325 --> 00:34:54.457
There you go.

712
00:34:57.764 --> 00:35:00.003
We know that was a lot
to put you through.

713
00:35:00.027 --> 00:35:02.310
but we had to make it look real.

714
00:35:02.334 --> 00:35:04.118
You needed to hear the truth from Ali.

715
00:35:06.963 --> 00:35:10.623
How does it work. being your asset?

716
00:35:10.647 --> 00:35:14.452
Well. uh. if something comes
across your desk

717
00:35:14.476 --> 00:35:16.585
or somebody makes contact
you don't know.

718
00:35:16.609 --> 00:35:19.327
or even if you just have
a feeling in your gut.

719
00:35:19.351 --> 00:35:22.286
you give us a call.
and we'll work it out together.

720
00:35:22.310 --> 00:35:23.810
Why not Kerem?

721
00:35:23.834 --> 00:35:25.507
You've already turned his head.

722
00:35:25.531 --> 00:35:27.204
Kerem got us this far.

723
00:35:27.228 --> 00:35:29.642
All he cared about was your safety.

724
00:35:29.666 --> 00:35:31.121
But with his drinking and drug use.

725
00:35:31.145 --> 00:35:32.645
we're concerned about his health.

726
00:35:32.669 --> 00:35:34.603
But we can get him treatment.

727
00:35:34.627 --> 00:35:36.344
- Yeah. of course.
- Yeah.

728
00:35:36.368 --> 00:35:38.694
You help us. we'll help you.

729
00:35:38.718 --> 00:35:41.088
Uh. I'll think about it.

730
00:35:41.112 --> 00:35:44.543
- Of course.
- Yeah.

731
00:35:47.988 --> 00:35:50.097
Our team will escort you
to the airfield.

732
00:35:50.121 --> 00:35:52.055
make sure you get home safely.

733
00:35:58.520 --> 00:35:59.889
Right.

734
00:35:59.913 --> 00:36:01.804
I'm off home for a hot soak. I think.

735
00:36:01.828 --> 00:36:04.285
- Long day.
- Aren't they all?

736
00:36:04.309 --> 00:36:06.591
Yeah.

737
00:36:40.867 --> 00:36:42.192
Hey. Bill. What's up?

738
00:36:42.216 --> 00:36:43.411
Need you to run an address.

739
00:36:43.435 --> 00:36:45.935
6435 Skillman Avenue. Long Island City.

740
00:36:45.959 --> 00:36:48.068
You know there are.
like. nine other people

741
00:36:48.092 --> 00:36:50.113
you should have asked before me. right?

742
00:36:50.137 --> 00:36:51.680
This is highly sensitive.
if you know what I mean.

743
00:36:51.704 --> 00:36:53.445
Yeah. yeah.

744
00:36:54.054 --> 00:36:56.772
OK. yeah. Got a hit.

745
00:36:56.796 --> 00:36:59.035
OK. it's the former address of a hacker.

746
00:36:59.059 --> 00:37:02.125
- alias Kinski.
- Kinski?

747
00:37:02.149 --> 00:37:03.692
She's still operating?
I thought we took her out.

748
00:37:03.716 --> 00:37:05.259
Well. we swept her up last year

749
00:37:05.283 --> 00:37:06.695
under investigation of orchestrating

750
00:37:06.719 --> 00:37:08.001
the Benson Mutual breach.

751
00:37:08.025 --> 00:37:09.132
Couldn't secure an indictment.

752
00:37:09.156 --> 00:37:10.830
Jubal. if he's working with her.

753
00:37:10.854 --> 00:37:12.788
it's to break into the CIA mainframe.

754
00:37:12.812 --> 00:37:15.225
- Maybe he's headed there next.
- Uh. OK.

755
00:37:15.249 --> 00:37:20.013
Uh. well. look. whatever
you're thinking of doing.

756
00:37:20.037 --> 00:37:21.666
just be careful.

757
00:37:21.690 --> 00:37:23.425
Oh. so you're saying don't get caught?

758
00:37:24.258 --> 00:37:27.312
Yeah. It's good advice. right?

759
00:38:12.741 --> 00:38:14.284
Colin!

760
00:38:16.397 --> 00:38:20.448
Turn around slowly.

761
00:38:21.315 --> 00:38:23.618
Let me see your hands.

762
00:38:24.362 --> 00:38:25.774
Bill. what are you doing?

763
00:38:25.798 --> 00:38:26.993
Why have you pulled a gun on me?

764
00:38:27.017 --> 00:38:29.125
So how's this whole thing work?
You steal information from the CIA.

765
00:38:29.149 --> 00:38:30.431
then drop it off here at Pyramid?

766
00:38:30.455 --> 00:38:32.346
What. you think I've gone dark. do you?

767
00:38:32.370 --> 00:38:34.827
I followed you from Kinski's.

768
00:38:34.851 --> 00:38:37.716
Well. that's very impressive.
I didn't feel you at all.

769
00:38:39.159 --> 00:38:40.920
So come on then.
What do you think you know?

770
00:38:40.944 --> 00:38:42.804
Well. I know about Sarah.

771
00:38:43.642 --> 00:38:45.270
Right.

772
00:38:47.080 --> 00:38:49.929
So. Sarah. Kinski. Pyramid.
you've been joining the dots.

773
00:38:49.953 --> 00:38:52.322
- Is it you?
- Is what me?

774
00:38:52.346 --> 00:38:54.315
Don't mess with me.

775
00:38:55.567 --> 00:38:57.277
Are you the mole?

776
00:38:57.830 --> 00:38:59.590
Is that what you think?

777
00:38:59.614 --> 00:39:01.614
You think I'm a mole?

778
00:39:02.879 --> 00:39:04.701
It certainly looks that way.

779
00:39:05.490 --> 00:39:07.163
No. Bill.

780
00:39:07.187 --> 00:39:08.904
No. I'm not.

781
00:39:08.928 --> 00:39:10.253
But I've got a funny feeling

782
00:39:10.277 --> 00:39:12.751
we might be looking for the same person.

783
00:39:13.150 --> 00:39:16.825
So why don't you just put
the gun back in your holster

784
00:39:16.849 --> 00:39:19.610
and let's have a civilized
conversation. shall we?

785
00:39:19.634 --> 00:39:22.526
'Cause I think we've got
a lot of work to do. mate.
